This is my emacs configuration. Feel free to clone.

Libraries and modes:

1) malabar: A great replacement for JDEE that supports maven and Java 1.5 generics (see https://github.com/espenhw/malabar-mode)
2) yaml: Yml mode (see http://tweedle-dee.org/svn/emacs.d/site-lisp/yaml-mode.el)
3) rinary: Ruby mode (see http://github.com/eschulte/rinari)
4) project-root: Provides support for other libraries and mode to do project management (see http://piranha.org.ua/project-root/)
5) cedet: The library that comes with emacs 23 is missing some features (see http://cedet.sourceforge.net/)
6) scala: Only syntax highlighting for scala